<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,980,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is generally similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moulton" authorityYear="1928" box="[751,887,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fungosus">
<emphasis box="[751,887,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">H. fungosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has the ocelli region without sculpture, the compound eyes with more facets, the prosternal ferna of major males greatly enlarged, the prosternal basantra absent in females, and the fore tarsus of females with a small tooth.
</paragraph>
